n - 1, -1, -1):\n            while stack and arr[stack[-1]] > arr[i]:\n                stack.pop()\n            right[i] = stack[-1] - i - 1 if stack else n - i - 1\n            stack.append(i)\n\n        # Calculate the result\n        result = 0\n        for i in range(n):\n            result = (result + arr[i] * (left[i] + 1) * (right[i] + 1)) % MOD\n\n        return result\n```\n\nThis solution uses a monotonic stack to efficiently find the number of subarrays for which each element is the minimum from both the left and right sides. This allows us to compute the contribution of each element to the final sum in O(n) time.", "estimated_date": 1537056000000}